626|"serving the altar and living by the altar, make the true body of"|FALSE
626|"Christ, wherein God Himself has honoured you not only above the laity,"|FALSE
626|"but even a little higher than the angels.  For to whom of His angels"|FALSE
626|"has He said at any time:  Thou art a priest for ever after the order of"|FALSE
626|"Melchisedech?  Ye dispense the patrimony of the crucified one to the"|FALSE
626|"poor, wherein it is required of stewards that a man be found faithful."|FALSE
626|"Ye are shepherds of the Lord's flock, as well in example of life as in"|FALSE
626|"the word of doctrine, which is bound to repay you with milk and wool."|FALSE
626|"Who are the givers of all these things, O clerks?  Is it not books?  Do"|FALSE
626|"ye remember therefore, we pray, how many and how great liberties and"|FALSE
626|"privileges are bestowed upon the clergy through us?  In truth, taught"|FALSE
626|"by us who are the vessels of wisdom and intellect, ye ascend the"|FALSE
626|"teacher's chair and are called of men Rabbi.  By us ye become"|FALSE
626|"marvellous in the eyes of the laity, like great lights in the world,"|FALSE
626|"and possess the dignities of the Church according to your various"|FALSE
626|"stations.  By us, while ye still lack the first down upon your cheeks,"|FALSE
