626|"and fetters, and are kept to be punished by a most shameful death."|FALSE
626|"Then your friend is put far away, nor is there any to mourn your lot."|FALSE
626|"Peter swears that he knows not the man: the people cry to the judge:"|FALSE
626|"Crucify, crucify Him!  If thou let this man go, thou act not Caesar's"|FALSE
626|"friend.  Now all refuge has perished, for ye must stand before the"|FALSE
626|"judgment-seat, and there is no appeal, but only hanging is in store for"|FALSE
626|"you. While the wretched man's heart is thus filled with woe and only"|FALSE
626|"the sorrowing Muses bedew their cheeks with tears, in his strait is"|FALSE
626|"heard on every side the wailing appeal to us, and to avoid the danger"|FALSE
626|"of impending death he shows the slight sign of the ancient tonsure"|FALSE
626|"which we bestowed upon him, begging that we may be called to his aid"|FALSE
626|"and bear witness to the privilege bestowed upon him.  Then straightway"|FALSE
626|"touched with pity we run to meet the prodigal son and snatch the"|FALSE
626|"fugitive slave from the gates of death.  The book he has not forgotten"|FALSE
