626|"he reads a few words, the power of the judge is loosed, the accuser is"|FALSE
626|"withdrawn, and death is put to flight.  O marvellous virtue of an"|FALSE
626|"empiric verse!  O saving antidote of dreadful ruin!  O precious reading"|FALSE
626|"of the psalter, which for this alone deserves to be called the book of"|FALSE
626|"life! Let the laity undergo the judgment of the secular arm, that"|FALSE
626|"either sewn up in sacks they may be carried out to Neptune, or planted"|FALSE
