626|"charge."|FALSE
626|"Again, we complain of another sort of injury which is too often"|FALSE
626|"unjustly inflicted upon our persons.  We are sold for bondmen and"|FALSE
626|"bondwomen, and lie as hostages in taverns with no one to redeem us.  We"|FALSE
626|"fall a prey to the cruel shambles, where we see sheep and cattle"|FALSE
626|"slaughtered not without pious tears, and where we die a thousand times"|FALSE
626|"from such terrors as might frighten even the brave.  We are handed over"|FALSE
626|"to Jews, Saracens, heretics and infidels, whose poison we always dread"|FALSE
626|"above everything, and by whom it is well known that some of our parents"|FALSE
626|"have been infected with pestiferous venom.  In sooth, we who should be"|FALSE
626|"treated as masters in the sciences, and bear rule over the mechanics"|FALSE
626|"who should be subject to us, are instead handed over to the government"|FALSE
626|"of subordinates, as though some supremely noble monarch should be"|FALSE
626|"trodden under foot by rustic heels.  Any seamster or cobbler or tailor"|FALSE
626|"or artificer of any trade keeps us shut up in prison for the luxurious"|FALSE
626|"and wanton pleasures of the clergy."|FALSE
626|"Now we would pursue a new kind of injury by which we suffer alike in"|FALSE
626|"person and in fame, the dearest thing we have.  Our purity of race is"|FALSE
626|"diminished every day, while new authors' names are imposed upon us by"|FALSE
626|"worthless compilers, translators, and transformers, and losing our"|FALSE
626|"ancient nobility, while we are reborn in successive generations, we"|FALSE
626|"become wholly degenerate; and thus against our will the name of some"|FALSE
626|"wretched stepfather is affixed to us, and the sons are robbed of the"|FALSE
626|"names of their true fathers.  The verses of Virgil, while he was yet"|FALSE
626|"living, were claimed by an impostor; and a certain Fidentinus"|FALSE
626|"mendaciously usurped the works of Martial, whom Martial thus deservedly"|FALSE
626|"rebuked:"|FALSE
626|"       \"The book you read is, Fidentinus! mine,"|FALSE
626|"  Though read so badly, 't well may pass for thine!\""|FALSE
626|"What marvel, then, if when our authors are dead clerical apes use us to"|FALSE
