626|"of Babel, if but one kind of speech had been transmitted by the whole"|FALSE
626|"human race."|FALSE
626|"We will add the last clause of our long lament, though far too short"|FALSE
626|"for the materials that we have. For in us the natural use is changed to"|FALSE
626|"that which is against nature, while we who are the light of faithful"|FALSE
