626|"It is naught, it is naught, saith every buyer.  But in vain; for behold"|FALSE
626|"how good and how pleasant it is to gather together the arms of the"|FALSE
626|"clerical warfare, that we may have the means to crush the attacks of"|FALSE
626|"heretics, if they arise."|FALSE
626|"Further, we are aware that we obtained most excellent opportunities of"|FALSE
