626|"case of need, and never refused to them the shelter of our favour,"|FALSE
626|"wherefore we deserved to find them most special furtherers of our"|FALSE
626|"wishes and promoters thereof in act and deed, who compassing land and"|FALSE
626|"sea, traversing the circuit of the world, and ransacking the"|FALSE
626|"universities and high schools of various provinces, were zealous in"|FALSE
626|"combatting for our desires, in the sure and certain hope of reward."|FALSE
626|"What leveret could escape amidst so many keen-sighted hunters?  What"|FALSE
